name: Patagonia
description: Patagonia is a globally recognized outdoor apparel and gear company known for its commitment to environmental and social responsibility. Founded in 1973 by Yvon Chouinard, the company designs high-quality, sustainable outdoor clothing and equipment. Patagonia is dedicated to using business as a force for positive change, focusing on reducing environmental impact and promoting ethical practices in its supply chain. The brand is a certified B Corporation and a member of 1% for the Planet, donating a portion of its revenue to environmental causes.
qualifications: Deep interest in environmental stewardship and sustainable practices
Active engagement in outdoor sports or related activities
Commitment to Social and Environmental Responsibility

name: Fjällräven
description: Fjällräven is a Swedish company specializing in outdoor clothing and equipment, Renowned for its durable and functional products designed for activities like trekking and hiking. Founded in 1960 by Åke Nordin, the company has a strong commitment to sustainability and timeless Swedish design. Fjällräven's dedication to sustainability is evident in their use of eco-friendly materials and ethical production practices, aiming to create products that last for generations and minimize environmental impact. Fjällräven has been recognized as the most sustainable brand in its industry in Sweden for multiple years, reflecting its commitment to sustainability.

name: Cotopaxi
description: Utah-based outdoor gear and apparel company founded in 2014 by Davis Smith and Stephan Jacob. The company is renowned for its commitment to social impact and sustainability, operating under the ethos of "Gear for Good." Cotopaxi allocates 1% of its annual revenue to the Cotopaxi Foundation, supporting initiatives aimed at alleviating poverty, particularly in Latin America. The foundation focuses on health care, education, and livelihood programs, partnering with organizations like the International Rescue Committee (IRC) and United to Beat Malaria. The company utilizes recycled, repurposed, or responsibly sourced materials in over 96% of its products and collaborates with factories that prioritize fair labor practices. The company has received recognition for its purpose-driven mission, ranking #339 on Forbes' list of America's Best Startup Employers in 2024.

name: The Common Good Company
description: An Australian apparel and merchandise brand dedicated to sustainable and ethical manufacturing practices. Specializing in garments made from 100% recycled materials, TCGCo aims to provide eco-friendly alternatives to traditional apparel, thereby reducing the environmental impact associated with the fashion industry. TCGCo meets rigorous standards of social and environmental performance, accountability, and transparency. The company emphasizes the use of recycled pre-consumer textile waste and recycled polyester in its products, significantly minimizing waste, water usage, and pollution compared to conventional manufacturing processes. The company also supports zero-waste initiatives and gender-responsive workplaces, further contributing to its mission of operating 'in the benefit or interest of all. TCGCo provides wholesale services, including screen printing and customization, catering to businesses and organizations seeking ethically produced merchandise. By focusing on planet, people, and production, The Common Good Company strives to meet present needs without compromising the ability of future generations to meet theirs.

name: Sozy
description: Female-founded clothing brand based in Encinitas, California, specializing in soft and cozy women's apparel designed for everyday wear. Established by Lanai Moliterno in 2019, the company emphasizes comfort and style. The company donates 10% of its profits to support survivors of sexual violence and partners with organizations like RAINN (Rape, Abuse & Incest National Network) to further this mission. Sozy's products are made in the USA, ensuring ethical manufacturing practices and supporting local communities. The brand is also Climate Neutral Certified, having measured and offset its greenhouse gas emissions by investing in carbon reduction and removal projects such as clean energy and reforestation.

name: Someone Somewhere
description: A sustainable and ethical fashion brand founded in 2016, headquartered in Mexico City, Mexico. The company collaborates with over 300 artisans across seven of Mexico's poorest states, integrating traditional handcrafts into contemporary clothing and accessories. Their product range includes jackets, sweatshirts, backpacks, t-shirts, masks, hats, and laptop cases, all designed to blend quality with cultural heritage. Someone Somewhere aims to alleviate poverty by providing fair and consistent job opportunities to artisans, preserving millenary traditions through enduring goods. By connecting conscious consumers and corporations with artisans, the company has supported more than 3,000 indigenous artisans, achieving an average 300% increase in their monthly income. Someone Somewhere has been awarded the Silver Medal by EcoVadis, reflecting its commitment to environmental and social responsibility.

name: Paka
description: Founded in the Andean region of Peru, The company is centered on crafting premium clothing using alpaca fiber, a natural, renewable, and biodegradable material prized for its softness, durability, and thermal properties. By blending traditional Andean craftsmanship with modern design, Paka creates versatile garments designed for outdoor and everyday wear. The company's mission extends beyond producing high-quality clothing—it actively empowers indigenous Quechua artisans, fosters sustainable practices, and promotes cultural preservation. Paka’s business model emphasizes environmental stewardship and ethical labor practices, striving to reduce its impact on the planet while supporting vulnerable communities.

name: united by blue
description: A sustainable lifestyle brand founded in 2010, headquartered in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. The company designs and sells eco-friendly apparel, bags, and accessories for both urban and outdoor adventurers. What sets United By Blue apart is its unwavering commitment to environmental conservation, innovative use of sustainable materials, and a mission-driven business model focused on reducing plastic pollution in oceans and waterways. United By Blue operates on a simple yet powerful mission: “For every product sold, we remove one pound of trash from oceans and waterways.” This initiative directly ties customer purchases to measurable environmental impact, creating a tangible link between business success and ecological restoration. United By Blue is more than just a clothing and accessories brand. It represents a movement toward sustainable and ethical business practices that prioritize the planet and its people. By integrating environmental restoration into its core business model, UBB has successfully aligned profit with purpose, proving that companies can thrive while making the world a better place.

name: Jetty
description: Founded in 2003 by a group of friends from New Jersey who shared a passion for surfing, fishing, art, travel, and music. With an initial investment of $200 each, they aimed to "draw their own line" in the apparel industry, creating products that resonate with those who love the water and the coastal lifestyle. Their products are known for unique designs that reflect the coastal lifestyle and are crafted with durability and comfort in mind. They prioritize eco-friendly practices, including the use of water-based inks in their screen-printing processes. In 2013, Jetty established the Jetty Rock Foundation, a 501(c)(3) charitable organization, to support coastal communities through various initiatives, including disaster relief efforts and environmental conservation. The foundation has donated over $1 million to these causes, reflecting Jetty's dedication to giving back to the community. Jetty's mission is to create kinship and community through a shared passion for water. Their tagline, "Draw Your Own Line®," embodies the brand's ethos of individuality and adventure, encouraging customers to pursue their passions and embrace the coastal lifestyle.

name: Dolphin Blue, Inc
description: A Dallas-based certified B Corporation specializing in environmentally responsible office supplies and products. The company emphasizes sustainability by offering items containing at least 10% post-consumer recycled material or those manufactured to exceed environmental standards, all with a minimal carbon footprint. Their product range includes paper goods, office and facility supplies, remanufactured ink and toner cartridges, and various home and garden items. Dolphin Blue is committed to responsible stewardship of Earth's resources, aiming to make sustainable purchasing simple and affordable for businesses and individuals. The company supports initiatives that promote sustainability, energy alternatives, organic agriculture, and waste reduction. They are associated with organizations such as the American Sustainable Business Council, Carbonfund.org, and the EPA Green Power Partner. Dolphin Blue's dedication to sustainability and quality has established it as a trusted source for environmentally and socially responsible products, contributing to a healthier, sustainable planet.

name: Seventh Generation
description: A leading brand in sustainable household and personal care products, committed to creating a healthy, sustainable future for the next seven generations. Founded in 1988, the company is a pioneer in producing environmentally friendly products, including plant-based cleaners, biodegradable laundry detergents, recycled paper goods, and hypoallergenic baby care items. Seventh Generation emphasizes transparency, using non-toxic ingredients and listing all product components on their labels. They are certified as a B Corporation, showcasing their dedication to social and environmental responsibility. The company is also an advocate for climate justice, renewable energy, and reducing plastic waste, striving to create products that are safe for people, pets, and the planet. Seventh Generation’s mission goes beyond profit, focusing on creating a positive impact through responsible sourcing, cruelty-free testing, and their commitment to renewable energy initiatives.

name: King Arthur Baking
description: King Arthur Baking Company, founded in 1790, is an employee-owned business that has become a trusted leader in the world of baking. With over two centuries of experience, King Arthur Baking is committed to providing high-quality baking products, tools, and educational resources to inspire and empower bakers of all levels. Renowned for its unbleached, non-GMO flours and a diverse range of baking essentials, the company prioritizes sustainability and social responsibility in every aspect of its operations. As a certified B Corporation, King Arthur Baking upholds rigorous standards for environmental performance, ethical sourcing, and employee welfare. The company is also dedicated to promoting inclusivity, community support, and food education through various programs and partnerships. King Arthur Baking is more than a brand—it’s a community of passionate bakers who believe in the power of baking to bring people together.

name: Uncommon Goods
description: A unique online marketplace that offers creatively designed, ethically sourced, and sustainably made products. Founded in 1999 and headquartered in Brooklyn, New York, the company curates an eclectic selection of gifts, home décor, jewelry, and personal accessories that celebrate individuality and creativity. Committed to social responsibility, Uncommon Goods ensures that all its products are made with the environment and workers in mind. The company is a Certified B Corporation, adhering to the highest standards of social and environmental impact. From supporting independent artists and small businesses to offering handcrafted, recycled, and organic items, Uncommon Goods strives to provide meaningful, high-quality products. With a mission to do good while delivering the extraordinary, Uncommon Goods donates a portion of every purchase to nonprofit organizations through its Better to Give program, empowering customers to make a difference with every order.

name: Numi
description: A globally recognized brand dedicated to crafting high-quality, organic, and sustainable teas that nourish the body and uplift the spirit. Founded in 1999 by a brother-and-sister duo, Numi is committed to blending premium, full-leaf teas, herbs, and spices without artificial flavorings or fragrances. Rooted in a passion for health and sustainability, Numi sources its ingredients directly from Fair Trade Certified and ethically responsible farms, ensuring equitable treatment of workers and fostering environmental stewardship. All products are USDA Organic, Non-GMO Project Verified, and made with biodegradable or recyclable packaging, making them as kind to the planet as they are to tea lovers. Driven by its mission to create lasting positive impact, Numi donates to water access projects and advocates for climate-friendly practices, making every cup a celebration of sustainability and social responsibility.

name: Better World Books
description: A socially responsible online bookstore that combines a love for books with a mission to make a global impact. Founded in 2002, the company provides an extensive selection of new and used books while promoting literacy and sustainability. Every purchase helps fund global literacy programs, with a portion of sales going directly to nonprofit organizations. Better World Books is committed to protecting the planet through environmentally friendly practices, including reusing and recycling books to reduce waste. They offer carbon-neutral shipping and have diverted millions of books from landfills. As a Certified B Corporation, Better World Books demonstrates its dedication to social and environmental performance, accountability, and transparency. With every book bought or donated, Better World Books turns the page toward a better world, making it a favorite for readers who value purpose-driven businesses.

name: Alima Pure
description: A pioneering beauty brand dedicated to creating high-performing, natural makeup products that empower confidence while prioritizing sustainability. Founded in 2004, the company is renowned for its minimalist approach, using clean, non-toxic ingredients without compromising on quality or performance. Alima Pure’s products are crafted to enhance natural beauty, with an extensive range of shades and formulations designed for all skin types and tones. Committed to sustainability, Alima Pure uses refillable packaging, carbon-neutral shipping, and ethical sourcing practices to minimize its environmental impact. As a Certified B Corporation, the brand upholds rigorous standards of social and environmental responsibility, ensuring that beauty lovers can feel good about their choices. Alima Pure believes that beauty doesn’t have to come at the cost of the planet, delivering products that are as kind to the environment as they are to your skin.

name: All Good
description: All Good Body Care is a sustainable wellness brand dedicated to creating high-quality, eco-friendly, and effective personal care products. Their product line includes organic balms, lotions, sunscreens, and lip care items crafted with natural, non-toxic, and cruelty-free ingredients. With a commitment to environmental responsibility, All Good Body Care ensures that all their packaging is recyclable, and they prioritize using reef-safe and biodegradable formulas to protect ecosystems. Certified as a B Corporation, All Good Body Care supports fair labor practices, ethical sourcing, and environmental restoration initiatives, embodying a mission to "do all good" for people and the planet.

name: Warby Parker
description: Known for providing high-quality, stylish, and affordable eyeglasses, sunglasses, and contacts. The company revolutionized the eyewear industry by introducing a direct-to-consumer model and a home try-on program, where customers can try five frames for free. Warby Parker emphasizes a socially conscious approach, with their "Buy a Pair, Give a Pair" program that donates glasses to individuals in need globally.

name: Preserve
description: A leader in sustainable household goods, offering eco-friendly products made from 100% recycled materials. From toothbrushes and razors to kitchenware and food storage, Preserve focuses on reducing waste and promoting a circular economy. Their innovative recycling program, Gimme 5, encourages customers to recycle #5 plastics, which are then transformed into new Preserve products.

name: Aisle
description: A trailblazer in sustainable menstrual care, offering eco-friendly, reusable period products that are good for your body and the planet. Their innovative lineup includes washable pads, period underwear, and accessories designed for comfort, durability, and effectiveness. Aisle products are crafted with sustainable materials such as organic cotton and recycled fibers, ensuring a smaller environmental footprint. With a commitment to inclusivity and body positivity, Aisle empowers individuals to make eco-conscious choices without compromising on performance or style.

name: Sea To Table
description: A leader in sustainable seafood, connecting consumers and chefs to wild-caught fish directly from American fisheries. Committed to preserving marine ecosystems and supporting local fishing communities, Sea to Table ensures traceability and transparency in every catch. Their seafood is responsibly harvested, flash-frozen for freshness, and shipped directly to your doorstep. With a focus on sustainability, they only source from fisheries that meet rigorous environmental standards, ensuring a better future for the ocean and the communities that depend on it.

name: Kleen Kanteen
description: A family-owned business that revolutionized the reusable drinkware industry with its durable, eco-friendly stainless steel bottles and containers. Founded in 2004, Klean Kanteen was one of the first companies to address the growing need for sustainable alternatives to single-use plastic bottles. The company's product lineup includes water bottles, insulated tumblers, food containers, and accessories, all designed to reduce waste and promote a healthier planet. Klean Kanteen is deeply committed to sustainability, using responsibly sourced materials and giving back to environmental initiatives through partnerships with non-profits.

name: Karün
description: A visionary eyewear brand redefining the industry with a deep commitment to sustainability and social responsibility. Founded in Patagonia, Karün creates stylish, high-quality eyewear using materials sourced from recycled and natural resources, such as discarded fishing nets, metals, and plastics. By partnering with local communities in Patagonia, Karün not only reduces waste but also empowers people to protect the natural environment. Each purchase supports conservation efforts and community-driven initiatives, making Karün more than an eyewear company—it's a movement for change.

name: Cielo Hammocks
description: A socially conscious brand offering beautifully handcrafted hammocks made by artisans in the Yucatán Peninsula. Combining traditional Mayan weaving techniques with contemporary designs, Cielo Hammocks delivers unparalleled comfort and durability while celebrating Mexican heritage and craftsmanship. The company is committed to empowering local artisans by providing fair wages, ethical working conditions, and access to global markets. Each purchase helps sustain communities and preserve traditional weaving practices, making Cielo Hammocks more than a product—it’s a story of cultural pride and social impact.

name: The Refill Shoppe
description: An innovative eco-friendly store committed to reducing waste by offering sustainable, refillable alternatives to everyday products. Located in Ventura, California, The Refill Shoppe provides a unique shopping experience where customers can refill containers with household and personal care items, minimizing single-use plastic consumption. Their diverse product selection includes soaps, shampoos, cleaning supplies, and lotions, all sourced from environmentally conscious brands. By promoting a circular economy, The Refill Shoppe empowers individuals to make greener choices for a healthier planet.

name: Ethique
description: A trailblazing zero-waste beauty and personal care brand committed to sustainability and innovation. Founded in New Zealand, Ethique offers a range of solid, plastic-free products, including shampoos, conditioners, skincare, and body care. Their eco-friendly alternatives eliminate the need for single-use plastic bottles, reducing waste without compromising on quality or performance. Ethique’s products are made with ethically sourced, vegan, and cruelty-free ingredients, ensuring they are kind to both people and the planet. The company’s dedication to sustainability extends beyond their products, as they plant trees and support environmental and social causes worldwide.

name: Bellroy
description: A globally recognized brand specializing in stylish, functional, and sustainably crafted carry goods. From wallets and backpacks to phone cases and travel essentials, Bellroy combines innovative design with premium materials to create products that enhance everyday life. With a focus on durability, utility, and sustainability, Bellroy ensures each product is thoughtfully crafted to be both beautiful and practical. Bellroy is deeply committed to reducing its environmental footprint by using eco-friendly materials like recycled fabrics, responsibly sourced leather, and plant-based alternatives. As a Certified B Corporation, Bellroy balances profit with purpose, emphasizing transparency, environmental responsibility, and positive social impact.

name: Dr. Bronner's
description: A renowned family-owned brand celebrated for its socially and environmentally responsible products, including organic and fair-trade soaps, personal care items, and cleaning products. With a legacy spanning over 70 years, Dr. Bronner’s is committed to creating high-quality, all-natural products that promote health, wellness, and sustainability. Each product is crafted using organic, vegan, and cruelty-free ingredients, ensuring safety for people and the planet. Dr. Bronner’s is also dedicated to activism, supporting fair trade, regenerative organic agriculture, and environmental justice initiatives worldwide.

name: Toms
description: A pioneering brand in ethical fashion and social entrepreneurship, recognized for its innovative 'One for One' model, where a pair of shoes is donated to someone in need for every pair purchased. Since its inception in 2006, TOMS has expanded its mission beyond shoes to include eyewear, coffee, and other products, funding impactful initiatives like providing clean water, supporting mental health, and improving educational opportunities. The company places sustainability at the heart of its operations by using eco-friendly materials, reducing waste, and ensuring fair labor practices throughout its supply chain. TOMS is also a Certified B Corporation, meeting the highest standards of social and environmental performance, transparency, and accountability. With every purchase, TOMS empowers communities and drives meaningful change, making it a leader in purpose-driven business.

name: Brew Dr. Kombucha
description: A trailblazer in the beverage industry, crafting authentic, organic kombucha with a commitment to sustainability and environmental stewardship. Founded in Portland, Oregon, Brew Dr. specializes in kombucha brewed with the highest-quality organic teas and botanicals, delivering vibrant, refreshing flavors while promoting gut health and wellness. Dedicated to eco-friendly practices, Brew Dr. Kombucha has implemented innovative sustainability initiatives, including sourcing organic ingredients, reducing waste, and achieving carbon neutrality. The company uses 100% renewable energy and partners with community organizations to support environmental conservation efforts. As a Certified B Corporation, Brew Dr. Kombucha upholds rigorous standards of social and environmental responsibility, making it a beverage company that truly embodies health and sustainability.

name: Stumptown Coffee Roasters
description: A pioneering specialty coffee company that has redefined how coffee is grown, sourced, and enjoyed. Founded in Portland, Oregon, Stumptown is committed to direct trade practices, building lasting relationships with farmers to ensure fair wages, sustainable practices, and exceptional quality. Their coffees are meticulously sourced from small, sustainable farms worldwide, resulting in unique, bold flavors that showcase the artistry of coffee cultivation. With a focus on environmental responsibility, Stumptown prioritizes sustainable packaging, carbon-conscious operations, and eco-friendly roasting practices. As a leader in ethical coffee production, Stumptown Coffee Roasters continues to set the standard for quality and sustainability in every cup, offering a truly elevated coffee experience while making a positive impact on the planet and farming communities.

name: Plaine Products
description: A revolutionary personal care brand committed to reducing plastic waste and promoting a circular economy. Offering a range of refillable, reusable, and recyclable aluminum bottles for shampoos, conditioners, body washes, and lotions, Plaine Products makes it easy to embrace a zero-waste lifestyle without compromising on quality or convenience. Every product is crafted with non-toxic, cruelty-free, and vegan ingredients, ensuring safe and effective care for both you and the environment. By prioritizing sustainability and partnering with ethical suppliers, Plaine Products empowers customers to join the fight against single-use plastics while enjoying premium personal care solutions. With a mission to make a meaningful impact on the planet, Plaine Products is redefining what it means to live sustainably, one bottle at a time.

name: Bombas
description: A mission-driven apparel company committed to delivering comfort and making a meaningful social impact. Known for its premium socks, underwear, and t-shirts, Bombas combines innovative design with high-quality materials to provide unmatched comfort and durability. With a core mission of 'buy one, give one,' Bombas donates an essential clothing item to those in need for every product purchased. To date, Bombas has donated millions of items to homeless shelters and organizations across the United States. The company also prioritizes sustainability by incorporating eco-friendly materials and practices into its production processes. As a Certified B Corporation, Bombas is dedicated to balancing profit with purpose, making it a leader in both quality and social responsibility.

name: Allbirds
description: A pioneering footwear and apparel brand known for its commitment to sustainability, comfort, and innovative design. Using natural, renewable materials such as merino wool, eucalyptus fiber, and sugarcane, Allbirds crafts products that are not only stylish but also environmentally friendly. With a focus on reducing their carbon footprint, Allbirds tracks, offsets, and publishes the carbon emissions of each product, striving for continuous improvement in sustainability. As a Certified B Corporation, Allbirds balances purpose and profit, leading the way in eco-friendly fashion. By combining ethical practices with cutting-edge materials, Allbirds delivers products that look good, feel good, and do good for the planet.

name: Who Gives A Crap
description: A purpose-driven brand revolutionizing everyday essentials with sustainability and humor. Specializing in eco-friendly toilet paper, tissues, and paper towels, the company uses 100% recycled materials or bamboo, creating high-quality products that are soft, strong, and sustainable. Beyond reducing environmental impact, Who Gives A Crap donates 50% of its profits to fund sanitation and clean water projects in developing communities around the world. With a commitment to plastic-free packaging, carbon-conscious operations, and ethical supply chains, Who Gives A Crap makes it easy to choose products that are good for you and the planet—while having a little fun along the way.

name: Only Natural Pet
description: A trusted leader in sustainable, holistic pet care, offering a wide range of high-quality, natural products for dogs and cats. Founded with the mission to provide healthier options for pets, the company focuses on natural ingredients, eco-friendly practices, and the well-being of pets and the planet. From biologically appropriate food and treats to holistic supplements, grooming products, and sustainable pet gear, Only Natural Pet ensures every product meets rigorous quality and environmental standards. A Certified B Corporation, the company is committed to carbon neutrality, ethical sourcing, and supporting a healthier future for pets and their families. With a passion for innovation and sustainability, Only Natural Pet empowers pet parents to make choices that are good for their furry friends and the planet.

name: Tom's of Maine
description: A pioneering brand in natural personal care, committed to creating safe, effective, and eco-friendly products for healthier living. Offering a wide range of natural toothpaste, deodorants, and body care items, the company ensures every product is made with high-quality, naturally derived ingredients. With a strong dedication to sustainability, Tom’s of Maine uses recyclable packaging, avoids artificial preservatives, colors, and flavors, and ensures cruelty-free testing. As a Certified B Corporation, the company balances purpose and profit by supporting environmental initiatives and donating 10% of its profits to nonprofit organizations. Tom’s of Maine empowers consumers to make natural, sustainable choices that benefit both their health and the planet.

name: Newly
description: A forward-thinking home goods and lifestyle brand that champions sustainability and timeless design. Dedicated to creating high-quality products from 100% recycled or repurposed materials, Newly offers a range of stylish and functional items, including glassware, textiles, and home décor. Every product is crafted with care, blending modern aesthetics with eco-friendly practices to minimize waste and environmental impact. As a Certified B Corporation, Newly is committed to transparency, ethical sourcing, and promoting a circular economy. By reimagining waste as a resource, Newly empowers customers to make conscious choices without compromising on style or durability. From your kitchen to your living space, Newly helps you live sustainably while enjoying products designed to last.

name: Bee's Wrap
description: A revolutionary alternative to plastic wrap, offering sustainable, reusable, and biodegradable food storage solutions. Made with organic cotton, beeswax, organic jojoba oil, and tree resin, Bee’s Wrap is designed to keep food fresh while reducing single-use plastic waste. Committed to protecting the planet, Bee’s Wrap is a Certified B Corporation that prioritizes sustainability at every level of production, from sourcing eco-friendly materials to minimizing environmental impact. With a mission to make sustainable living easy and accessible, Bee’s Wrap empowers individuals and households to embrace a zero-waste lifestyle without compromising on convenience or quality.

name: Bigelow Tea
description: A family-owned company renowned for crafting high-quality teas with a commitment to sustainability and community. Since 1945, Bigelow has offered a wide range of flavorful, expertly blended teas made with the finest ingredients. From classic favorites like Earl Grey and Chamomile to innovative herbal and green tea blends, Bigelow ensures every cup delivers exceptional taste and quality. Dedicated to protecting the planet, Bigelow Tea is a Certified B Corporation and a leader in sustainability initiatives, including zero-waste-to-landfill production and renewable energy usage. By prioritizing ethical sourcing, environmentally friendly practices, and community involvement, Bigelow Tea creates a tea experience that is good for you and good for the planet.

name: Proud Source Spring Water
description: A sustainably focused bottled water company that provides natural spring water in 100% recyclable aluminum bottles, offering a cleaner, eco-friendly alternative to single-use plastic. Sourced from pristine springs in the United States, Proud Source Water delivers crisp, refreshing hydration while minimizing its environmental footprint. Committed to sustainability, Proud Source Water operates with a zero-waste philosophy, supports local communities, and uses renewable energy in its production process. By prioritizing transparency, responsible sourcing, and eco-conscious packaging, Proud Source Water empowers consumers to make sustainable choices and protect the planet with every sip.

name: Frank And Oak
description: Founded in 2012 with a simple mission: to connect with a new generation of creatives and entrepreneurs. What began as a local favourite in Montreal’s Mile End quickly grew into one of Canada’s leading lifestyle brands. Over the years, Frank And Oak has intentionally shifted its focus toward responsible fashion. From sourcing sustainable materials to ensuring fair labour practices, we are committed to creating products that are good for people and for the planet.

name: Prose
description: A leading innovator in personalized hair care, crafting custom formulas tailored to your unique hair needs and goals. Using a comprehensive consultation process, Prose analyzes individual hair type, lifestyle, and environmental factors to create bespoke shampoos, conditioners, and treatments. Every product is made fresh with responsibly sourced, high-quality ingredients to ensure optimal performance and care. Committed to sustainability and transparency, Prose is a Certified B Corporation dedicated to reducing environmental impact through refillable packaging, carbon-neutral operations, and ethical sourcing. By combining science, sustainability, and personalization, Prose empowers customers to embrace hair care that’s as unique as they are.

name: Picture
description: A trailblazing outdoor apparel brand dedicated to sustainability, innovation, and performance. Founded in 2008, Picture offers a wide range of eco-friendly clothing, including jackets, snow pants, base layers, and accessories, designed for outdoor enthusiasts and adventurers. Every product is crafted with responsibly sourced materials, including organic cotton, recycled polyester, and bio-based fabrics, ensuring both durability and minimal environmental impact. As a Certified B Corporation, Picture Organic Clothing is committed to reducing its carbon footprint through sustainable manufacturing practices, renewable energy usage, and a dedication to a circular economy. With bold, stylish designs and a deep respect for the planet, Picture empowers individuals to enjoy the great outdoors while protecting it for future generations.

name: Rebel Green
description: A purpose-driven brand dedicated to creating eco-friendly household and personal care products that are safe for your family and the planet. Known for its biodegradable, plant-based formulas and plastic-conscious packaging, Rebel Green offers a wide range of products including laundry detergents, dish soaps, fresheners, and body care items. Committed to sustainability and transparency, Rebel Green uses natural ingredients that are free from harsh chemicals and synthetic fragrances. By prioritizing non-toxic, cruelty-free, and sustainable practices, Rebel Green empowers conscious consumers to make healthier, greener choices without compromising on performance or style.

name: World of Books
description: A sustainable and socially conscious company dedicated to giving pre-loved books a new life while reducing waste. As one of the largest online sellers of used books, World of Books connects readers with affordable, high-quality literature while promoting a circular economy. The company collects and resells books from various sources, ensuring they stay in circulation rather than ending up in landfills. Committed to sustainability, World of Books operates with a carbon-neutral footprint and contributes to literacy programs and environmental initiatives. With every purchase, customers support a greener future, making World of Books the go-to destination for eco-conscious readers worldwide.

name: Burton
description: A pioneering leader in the snowboard industry, renowned for its high-performance gear, innovative designs, and deep-rooted commitment to sustainability. Founded in 1977, Burton revolutionized snowboarding culture by creating cutting-edge equipment and apparel that enhances performance and inspires adventure. From snowboards and bindings to outerwear and accessories, Burton crafts products that cater to riders of all levels, ensuring durability and style on and off the slopes. As a Certified B Corporation, Burton is dedicated to protecting the environment through sustainable manufacturing, ethical labor practices, and a goal to achieve carbon neutrality. By integrating eco-friendly materials and supporting global initiatives for a healthier planet, Burton empowers riders to enjoy the mountains while preserving them for future generations

name: Nimble
description: A forward-thinking brand specializing in creating eco-friendly, high-performance tech accessories that blend sustainability with innovation. Offering a range of products including portable chargers, phone cases, and charging cables, Nimble is committed to using ethically sourced, recycled, and biodegradable materials to reduce electronic waste and environmental impact. As a Certified B Corporation, Nimble Technology prioritizes transparency, fair labor practices, and environmental stewardship. With every product purchase, Nimble funds e-waste recycling programs and provides a pre-paid envelope to help customers responsibly recycle old devices. Nimble empowers tech enthusiasts to make sustainable choices without compromising on quality or design.

name: Lomi
description: A groundbreaking brand revolutionizing home composting with its innovative, user-friendly countertop composters. Designed to turn food scraps, bioplastics, and other organic waste into nutrient-rich compost within hours, Lomi empowers individuals to reduce their household waste and contribute to a healthier planet. With its sleek, modern design and efficient technology, Lomi makes composting accessible and convenient for everyone. Committed to sustainability, Lomi reduces methane emissions from food waste while promoting soil health through its composting process. By blending cutting-edge innovation with eco-friendly practices, Lomi helps households close the loop on waste and create a cleaner, greener future.

name: KMD Brands
description: A global leader in outdoor and active lifestyle products, dedicated to inspiring people to explore and enjoy the outdoors while prioritizing sustainability and innovation. With a portfolio that includes renowned brands such as Kathmandu, Rip Curl, and Oboz, KMD Brands offers high-quality gear, apparel, and footwear designed for adventure seekers worldwide. Committed to reducing its environmental impact, KMD Brands integrates sustainable materials, ethical manufacturing practices, and community-driven initiatives across all its brands. By blending cutting-edge design with eco-conscious values, KMD Brands empowers customers to live their best outdoor lives while protecting the planet for future generations.

name: Vita Coco
description: A global leader in coconut-based beverages, offering refreshing and naturally hydrating products that promote a healthy, sustainable lifestyle. Best known for its 100% pure coconut water, Vita Coco sources fresh coconuts from small farms in tropical regions, ensuring exceptional taste and quality in every sip. With a diverse range of products, including flavored coconut waters, coconut oil, and plant-based beverages, Vita Coco caters to health-conscious consumers seeking natural alternatives. Committed to sustainability and social impact, Vita Coco supports local farming communities, invests in regenerative agriculture, and minimizes its environmental footprint through innovative packaging and responsible sourcing. By blending great taste with eco-conscious values, Vita Coco empowers customers to hydrate responsibly while giving back to the planet.

name: Too Good To Go
description: An innovative platform on a mission to fight food waste and create a more sustainable future. Through its user-friendly app, Too Good To Go connects users with local businesses—such as restaurants, bakeries, and grocery stores—offering surplus food at discounted prices. By rescuing perfectly good food that would otherwise go to waste, the platform empowers both consumers and businesses to save money and reduce their environmental impact. Operating in numerous countries worldwide, Too Good To Go has saved millions of meals and significantly reduced carbon emissions. Committed to sustainability and community impact, the platform inspires individuals to take action against food waste while supporting local businesses and fostering a greener planet.

name: Bird
description: A sustainable eyewear brand on a mission to create stylish, eco-friendly sunglasses while giving back to the planet. Crafted with innovative materials like FSC-certified wood, bio-based acetate, and recycled aluminum, Bird combines exceptional design with a commitment to environmental stewardship. Each pair of sunglasses is built to last, ensuring durability and timeless style for conscious consumers. As the first eyewear brand to become a Certified B Corporation in the UK, Bird Sunglasses is dedicated to ethical production, carbon neutrality, and supporting global communities. Through their Share Your Sun initiative, every purchase provides solar light to families in need, reducing reliance on harmful kerosene lamps. Bird Sunglasses empowers customers to look good, feel good, and do good for the planet.

name: The Good Tee
description: A purpose-driven clothing brand dedicated to creating ethically made, sustainable apparel that is as good for the planet as it is for the people who make it. Specializing in ultra-soft, responsibly sourced cotton basics, The Good Tee emphasizes transparency, fair trade practices, and eco-conscious production. From organic cotton T-shirts to versatile everyday wear, The Good Tee offers high-quality, durable garments that prioritize comfort and sustainability. Committed to making a positive impact, The Good Tee collaborates with Fairtrade-certified farmers, ensures ethical manufacturing, and uses eco-friendly packaging to reduce waste. By empowering conscious consumers to make better choices, The Good Tee aims to redefine the fashion industry and promote a more sustainable future.

name: ECOlunchbox
description: A mission-driven company dedicated to creating innovative, sustainable lunchware solutions designed to reduce the reliance on single-use plastics. Founded with a focus on environmental stewardship and health, ECOlunchbox offers a wide range of plastic-free, reusable food containers made from high-quality, food-grade stainless steel and silicone. Their products are not only eco-friendly but also non-toxic, BPA-free, and designed to be durable, making them a long-lasting alternative to disposable lunchware. The company’s product line includes versatile bento boxes, snack containers, and lunch accessories that cater to individuals, families, and schools committed to reducing their environmental footprint. ECOlunchbox's designs emphasize functionality and style, featuring stackable and leak-resistant options to suit diverse on-the-go lifestyles.

name: Charlotte's Web
description: A leading wellness company renowned for its high-quality hemp-derived CBD products. Founded in 2013 by the Stanley Brothers, Charlotte's Web was inspired by Charlotte Figi, a young girl with Dravet Syndrome whose seizures were significantly reduced using the company’s proprietary hemp extract. This transformative success story propelled the company to the forefront of the CBD industry. Charlotte's Web is committed to harnessing the natural benefits of hemp to improve lives. Their products are made from whole-plant hemp extracts containing a full spectrum of cannabinoids, terpenes, and flavonoids to maximize the "entourage effect." With a focus on quality and transparency, the company oversees the entire production process, from seed to shelf, to ensure their products meet rigorous standards.

name: mountainFLOW
description: An innovative company dedicated to creating eco-friendly and sustainable alternatives to traditional ski and snowboard waxes, which are often petroleum-based and harmful to the environment. Founded with a passion for outdoor recreation and environmental stewardship, MountainFlow produces plant-based, biodegradable waxes designed to deliver high performance without compromising nature. The company’s product line includes all-temperature and temperature-specific ski and snowboard waxes, as well as bike lubricants and skin waxes, all formulated with non-toxic, renewable ingredients. By offering a sustainable choice to outdoor enthusiasts, MountainFlow aims to reduce the environmental impact of outdoor sports while maintaining peak performance for athletes.

name: Amy's Kitchen
description: A family-owned company that specializes in organic, vegetarian, and plant-based meals made with wholesome, high-quality ingredients. Founded in 1987 by Rachel and Andy Berliner, Amy’s Kitchen was inspired by their desire to provide convenient, nutritious meals for people with busy lifestyles without compromising on taste or values. The company is named after their daughter, Amy. Known for its commitment to sustainability, Amy's Kitchen sources organic ingredients from trusted farmers, ensuring that their products are free from synthetic pesticides, GMOs, and artificial additives. Their extensive product line includes frozen entrees, soups, pizzas, burritos, and snacks, catering to a variety of dietary needs, including gluten-free, vegan, and dairy-free options.

name: Small Axe Peppers
description: A mission-driven hot sauce company that combines a love for bold flavors with a commitment to supporting local communities. Founded in 2014, the company partners with community gardens and urban farmers across the United States to grow the peppers used in their sauces. By sourcing directly from these gardens, Small Axe Peppers creates a unique farm-to-bottle experience while providing economic support to local growers. Known for their distinct flavor profiles, Small Axe Peppers hot sauces are crafted with fresh, high-quality ingredients, offering a perfect balance of heat and flavor. Their sauces are versatile, suitable for a wide range of culinary uses, and beloved by food enthusiasts for their artisanal quality.

name: Tillamook
description: A farmer-owned dairy cooperative based in Tillamook County, Oregon. Founded in 1909, Tillamook has grown to become one of the most recognized and respected dairy brands in the United States, known for its high-quality cheeses, ice creams, yogurts, butter, and other dairy products. Rooted in a tradition of craftsmanship and a commitment to excellence, Tillamook is guided by its farmer-owners, many of whom represent generations of dairy farming expertise. The cooperative prioritizes using milk from cows that are not treated with artificial growth hormones (rBST) and emphasizes sustainable farming and animal welfare practices.

name: Welly
description: A forward-thinking company specializing in innovative and stylish first aid and wellness products. Founded with the mission to make care essentials accessible, fun, and practical, Welly offers a modern twist on traditional first aid kits by combining functionality with vibrant, eye-catching designs. The company’s product lineup includes bandages, ointments, first aid kits, and other personal care items crafted to meet the needs of active, health-conscious individuals and families. Welly’s products are portable, organized, and packaged in sustainable materials, making them a convenient and eco-friendly choice for on-the-go lifestyles.

name: Goodly Gosh
description: Goodly Gosh is a family-owned business based in Perth, Western Australia, dedicated to providing plastic-free, non-toxic, ethically sourced, and sustainably made products. Founded by Yasmeen and Ali, the company emerged from their personal commitment to a healthier lifestyle and a desire to offer practical, eco-friendly alternatives to everyday items.
qualifications: Ethically Sourced and Sustainably Made Products

name: ButcherBox
description: A premium subscription-based meat delivery service that aims to make high-quality, sustainably sourced meats accessible to everyone. Founded in 2015 by Mike Salguero and headquartered in Watertown, Massachusetts, ButcherBox delivers a curated selection of meats directly to customers’ doorsteps. With a focus on transparency, ethical sourcing, and quality, ButcherBox partners with trusted farmers, ranchers, and fisheries to provide 100% grass-fed and grass-finished beef, free-range organic chicken, heritage-breed pork, and sustainably sourced seafood. At its core, ButcherBox is committed to offering meats that are better for the environment, the animals, and the people who consume them. By eliminating middlemen and working directly with producers, the company ensures traceability and adherence to high animal welfare standards. The meats are free of hormones, antibiotics, and unnecessary additives, catering to health-conscious consumers who value clean and responsibly sourced food.

name: Ocean Bottle
description: A purpose-driven company tackling the global plastic pollution crisis by combining innovative product design with impactful environmental action. Founded in 2019, the company creates high-quality, reusable water bottles that not only reduce single-use plastic waste but also fund the collection of ocean-bound plastic in some of the world’s most polluted coastal areas. Each Ocean Bottle purchased funds the collection of 11.4 kg (approximately 25 pounds) of plastic waste, equivalent to preventing 1,000 plastic bottles from entering the ocean. This unique business model enables Ocean Bottle to empower local communities by providing income opportunities for individuals in coastal regions, often in developing countries. Collected plastics are repurposed or recycled, ensuring a closed-loop system that mitigates environmental harm.

name: Stubble & 'Stache
description: a men's grooming brand founded in 2012 by Nicholas Karnaze, a former U.S. Marine. The company offers a range of skincare and beard care products designed to improve skin health and maintain facial hair. Their product line includes beard oils, moisturizers, and face and beard washes, all formulated to soothe irritation and itch associated with facial hair growth. As a service-disabled veteran-owned small business, Stubble & Stache donates a portion of its profits to charities supporting wounded veterans and their families, particularly those addressing post-traumatic stress and depression. All products are proudly made in the USA, emphasizing the company's dedication to quality and ethical manufacturing practices.

name: K9 Ballistics
description: Founded in 2010 and headquartered in Camarillo, California, specializes in manufacturing durable dog beds and accessories designed to withstand the rigors of active and chewing-prone dogs. Their product line includes chew-resistant beds, crate pads, and travel gear, all crafted with high-quality materials to ensure longevity and comfort for pets. As a Certified B Corporation since January 2021, K9 Ballistics demonstrates a commitment to social and environmental responsibility, focusing on sustainable manufacturing practices and the well-being of their employees, community, and the environment. The company incorporates post-consumer certified recycled fibers into their products, diverting millions of plastic bottles from landfills, and emphasizes ethical production methods throughout their supply chain.

name: Rumpl
description: Founded in 2014 by Wylie Robinson and based in Portland, Oregon, specializes in creating high-performance blankets and outdoor gear that blend comfort with durability. The company utilizes technical materials commonly found in premium outdoor products to craft versatile blankets suitable for both indoor and outdoor use. Their product line includes the Original Puffy Blanket, which has become synonymous with the brand, as well as other items like towels and ponchos designed for adventure seekers. The company has raised approximately $4.97 million in funding over three rounds, with the latest Series A round in August 2018 led by White Road Investments. Rumpl's dedication to innovation and sustainability has positioned it as a leader in the technical blanket category, appealing to consumers seeking functional and eco-friendly comfort solutions.

name: Happy Earth
description: A sustainable lifestyle apparel brand dedicated to environmental conservation and ethical production practices. Founded in 2016 by David Winters and Victoria Gennaro, the company offers a range of products, including organic t-shirts, sweatshirts, activewear, and accessories, all designed with a commitment to vegan, eco-friendly, and slow fashion principles. Happy Earth prioritizes the use of organic cotton and consciously avoids polyester to reduce microfiber pollution. Over 95% of its products are manufactured in Fair Trade certified factories, ensuring that workers' rights are upheld. The brand also uses recycled and recyclable packaging and empowers its customers to give back with every purchase by supporting initiatives such as tree planting, combating climate change, and removing trash from nature.

name: Blueland
description: A New York-based company revolutionizing conventional cleaning and personal care products by eliminating single-use plastic packaging. Founded in 2019 by Sarah Paiji Yoo and John Mascari, Blueland offers eco-friendly, refillable cleaning supplies designed to reduce environmental impact. Their product line includes cleaning sprays, hand soaps, dish soaps, laundry detergents, and personal care items, all utilizing reusable bottles and dissolvable tablets or powders. This innovative approach allows consumers to create effective cleaning solutions at home by simply adding water, thereby minimizing plastic waste and promoting sustainability. The company has garnered significant recognition for its commitment to environmental stewardship and has secured substantial funding to support its mission. As of February 2022, Blueland completed a Series B funding round, raising $20 million to further expand its product offerings and retail presence.

name: LifeStraw
description: Established in 1994 and headquartered in Baltimore, Maryland, is a leading manufacturer of water filtration and purification devices designed to provide safe drinking water across diverse environments. Originally developed by the Swiss-based company Vestergaard, LifeStraw's products have evolved from portable "straw" filters to a comprehensive range of solutions, including personal filters, water bottles with integrated filtration, and high-volume purifiers for family and community use. These devices effectively remove waterborne bacteria, parasites, microplastics, and, in advanced models, chemicals and heavy metals, ensuring access to clean water without the need for batteries or chemical treatments.
